<p class="lead">The responsive embed pattern automatically determines the dimensions of media content based on the width of the containers they are embedded in. A fixed ratio allows embedded content to scale appropriately on any device.</p>

<h2>Rules for responsive embed</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>To embed YouTube videos</strong> please use the <a href="../video/index.html">video pattern</a>.</li>
<li><strong>To embed SoundCloud files</strong> please use the <a href="../audio/index.html">audio pattern</a>.</li>
<li><strong>To embed Google maps</strong> please use the <a href="../google-maps/index.html">Google Maps pattern</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2>How to use</h2>
<p>This wrapper div must have two classes: <code>embed-responsive</code> class, and another that specifies its aspect ratio.</p>
<p>There are two ratios available:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>16:9</strong> <code>embed-responsive-16by9</code>. Use this to show videos, it is better suited for use with HD media.</li>
<li><strong>4:3</strong> <code>embed-responsive-4by3</code>.</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"&gt;
[iframe, embed, video or object with embed-responsive-item class]
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

<p>You don't need to include <code>frameborder="0"</code> in your <code>iframe</code> as Bootstrap overrides that for you.</p>

